---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Card from '../../components/Card.astro';
---

<Layout title="Math Adventures | Aarya Patel">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 space-y-6">

    <!-- Page Header -->
    <section class="text-center py-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">🧮 Math Adventures</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Exploring mathematics and problem-solving</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Kangaroo Math Experience - Growth Mindset -->
    <Card title="Kangaroo Math Competition" emoji="🏆">
      <p class="mb-4">In Grade 4, I participated in the Kangaroo Math competition for 4th graders!</p>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-slate-700 rounded-lg p-6 mb-4">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">My Result: 76/120</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Not as high as I hoped, but a great learning experience!</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-900/20 rounded-lg p-6 mb-4">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3 text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400">💡 What I Learned</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <li>
            <strong>Practice tests ≠ Real tests:</strong> I was scoring 110+ in practice, but the real competition felt different.
            Tests can be tricky even when you're well prepared!
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Test-taking is a skill:</strong> It's not just about knowing the material - it's about managing time,
            reading carefully, and staying calm under pressure.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Don't be discouraged:</strong> One test doesn't define my abilities. I learned so much just by preparing,
            and I'll do even better next time!
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        I'm proud of myself for trying, and I know that with more practice and experience,
        I'll continue to improve. Math competitions are a fun way to challenge myself!
      </p>
    </Card>

    <!-- Problem Solving -->
    <Card title="Problem Solving" emoji="🧩">
      <p class="mb-4">I love solving math problems! Here are some ways I practice:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        <li><strong>LeetCode:</strong> Coding problems that use math and logic</li>
        <li><strong>Creative Problem Solving book:</strong> Teaches me to think outside the box</li>
        <li><strong>Math competitions:</strong> Kangaroo Math and similar contests</li>
        <li><strong>School math:</strong> Always working to get better at fundamentals</li>
      </ul>
    </Card>

    <!-- What I Enjoy About Math -->
    <Card title="Why I Love Math" emoji="❤️">
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        <li>Math problems have clear answers - when you solve them, you know you're right!</li>
        <li>It teaches me to think logically and step-by-step</li>
        <li>There's always more to learn - from arithmetic to algebra to calculus</li>
        <li>Math is everywhere - in nature, in coding, in music!</li>
      </ul>
    </Card>

    <!-- Future Goals -->
    <Card title="Math Goals" emoji="🎯">
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        <li>Improve my test-taking skills for next year's competitions</li>
        <li>Continue practicing with problem-solving books</li>
        <li>Explore pre-algebra and algebra concepts in Grade 5</li>
        <li>Balance speed and accuracy in problem-solving</li>
      </ul>
    </Card>

    <!-- Back to Home -->
    <div class="text-center pt-4">
      <a href="/" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">← Back to Home</a>
    </div>

  </div>
</Layout>
